54.4	Aldebaran	Aldebaran	Aldebaran (α Tau, α Tauri, Alpha Tauri) is a red giant star located about 65 light years away in the zodiac constellation of Taurus. With an average apparent magnitude of 0.87 it is the brightest star in the constellation and is one of the brightest stars in the nighttime sky. The name Aldebaran is Arabic and translates literally as "the follower", presumably because this bright star appears to follow the Pleiades, or "Seven Sisters" star cluster in the night sky.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/31/Taurus_constellation_map.svg/250px-Taurus_constellation_map.svg.png
